text: Jeotgalicoccus pinnipedialis is a gram-positive bacterium. The cells are coccoid. Jeotgalicoccus pinnipediales is a facultative anaerobic bacteria: It growth under aerobic (oxygen is present) or anaerobic conditions (oxygen is not present). It was found in the swab of the mouth of a Southern elephant seal. It belongs to the Staphylococcaceae. ==References== Category:Gram- positive bacteria
title: Jeotgalicoccus pinnipedialis
